<item>
            <title>[LU-6552] MDS crash after recovery</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6552</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have upgraded my Lustre file system from 1.8.7 on Enterprise Linux 5 to 2.5.3 on EL6. After a few days, the MDS started crashing and now crashes every time I mount the MDT after the recovery is finished. this looks similar to the crash reported in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5040&quot; title=&quot;kernel BUG at fs/jbd2/transaction.c:1033&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5040&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5040&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, that&apos;s why I have applied the patch from that issue to my server. I have also added the patch from &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5777&quot; title=&quot;reserve enough credits for chown/chgrp operation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5777&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5777&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but the crash is the same.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>SL6.6</environment>
